\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 by Chris Lowney\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Of Jesuits and JP Morgan\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93poverty, as the strong wall of religious life, should be loved\'94\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Loyola and his colleagues were convinced that we perform our best in supportive, encouraging and positively charged environments, and he exhorted his managers to create environments within to have \'93greater love than fear.\'94\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Leadership is not reserved for a few Poo-Bahs sitting atop large companies, nor do leadership opportunities arise only \'93on stage\'94 at work\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 The four pillars of Jesuit success\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 self-awareness\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 ingenuity \
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 love\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 heroism\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 The Jesuits molded leaders who\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 understood their strengths, weaknesses, values, and worldview\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 confidently innovated and adapted to embrace a changing world\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 engaged others with a positive loving attitude\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 energized themselves and others through heroic ambitions\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 What Leaders Do\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 The leader who figures out where we need to go, points us in the right direction, gets us to agree that we need to get there, and rallies us through the inevitable obstacles that separate us from the promised land\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Jesuit leadership rejects quick-fix approaches that equate leadership with mere technique and tactics, scrapping \'93command and control\'94 models that rely on one great person to lead the rest\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 We\'92re all leaders, and we\'92re leading all the time, well or poorly\
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Leadership springs from within. It\'92s about who I am as much as what I do\
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Leadership is not an act. It is a way of living\
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Leadership is an asymptotic process\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 The Jesuit model explodes the \'93one great man\'94 model for the simple reason that everyone has influence, and everyone projects influence \'97 good or bad, large or small \'97 all the time\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 A person who understands what he or she wants, who is anchored by certain principles, and who faces the world with a consistent outlook. Leadership behavior develops naturally once this internal foundation has been laid. If it hasn\'92t been, mere technique can never compensate.\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 The jesuit way of proceeding is a compass, not a checklist. If you know where you\'92re heading, the compass is an infinitely more valuable instrument\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 By knowing what you value and what you want to achieve, you can orient yourself to any new environment, adapting confidently in unfamiliar circumstances\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Jesuit leaders became leaders by\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 understanding their strengths, weaknesses, values, and worldview\
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 confidently innovating and adapting to embrace a changing world\
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 engaging others with a positive, loving attitude\
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 energizing themselves and others through heroic ambitions\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93Leaders thrive by understanding who they are and what they value, by becoming aware of unhealthy blind spots or weaknesses that can derail them, and by cultivating the habit of continuous self-reflection and learning\'94\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Research increasingly suggests that IQ and technical skills are far less crucial to leadership success than mature self-awareness\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93Living with one foot raised\'94\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 A leader must rid himself of ingrained habits, prejudices, cultural preferences, and the \'93we\'92ve always done it this way\'94 attitude\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93Leaders face the world with a confident, healthy sense of themselves as endowed with talent, dignity, and the potential to lead. They find exactly these same attributes in others and passionately commit to honoring and unlocking the potential they find in themselves and in others. They create environments bound and energized by loyalty, affection and mutual support.\'94\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93Leaders imagine an inspiring future and strive to shape it rather than passively watching the future happen around them. Heroes extract gold from opportunities at hand rather than waiting for golden opportunities to be handed to them.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 An Accidental Company\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 Leaders are \'91born twice\'92 individuals who endure major events that lead to a sense of separateness, or perhaps estrangement, from their environments. As a result, they turn inward in order to reemerge with a created rather than an inherited sense of identity.\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 When Loyola was figuring out what he wanted to do, his self-awareness is what drew Europe\'92s finest to him.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Loyola\'92s core appeal was not his own leadership traits \'97 it was his ability to identify and unlock others\'92 latent leadership potential.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 One who truly lives under obedience is fully disposed to execute instantly and unhesitatingly whatever is enjoined him, no matter to him whether it be very hard to do.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93Un-interupted life of heroic deeds and heroic virtues\'94\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Loyola has virtually no tangible accomplishments to show for almost 2/3 of his life.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 Without the setbacks, crises, and challenges that punctuated Loyola\'92s real life, he might never have grappled with who he was, what we wanted, what personal resources he had, and why he had failed along the way. Only by asking and answering those questions does one develop personal leadership capacity.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 Success flows from the undying commitment and persistence of many, not the isolated efforts of one.\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Leadership Role Models\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Goes survived the worst of the journey, only to die a thousand miles short of Beijing. He never found the Kingdom of Cathay, because China was Cathay.\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 History readily celebrates those who literally put places on the map, however there is only a quick slide into oblivion for those who came away empty, or those like Goes, who removed places like Cathay from the map.\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 The measure of personal greatness is less what they found at journey\'92s end and more the depth of human character that carried them along the way: their imagination, will, perseverance, courage, resourcefulness and willingness to bear the risk of failure.\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Goes\'92 story re-defines leadership success by illustrating how one need not make a big, visible, self-aggrandizing \'91win\'92 to be successful; sometimes success in the form of a contribution that helps the team win.\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 \cf3 inculturation
\f1\b0 \cf0  \'97 assimilation of a host culture\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Jesuits should become experts not only in theology and philosophy, the discipline everyone expects priests to master, but also in languages, mathematics and the sciences\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93he relentlessly pursued his passion for astronomy throughout his remaining years\'94\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 \cf3 quixotic
\f1\b0 \cf0  \'97 exceedingly idealistic\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Scientists needed to accept the facts and set about finding a credible theory to explain them.\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 On Clavius S.J. \'85 \'93His writing is elegant, a simple testimony to his intellectual integrity and seemingly unwavering commitment to the truth\'94\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 None of the great leaders in the book ever managed more than a handful of others, they led themselves, they didn\'92t shrink from the task, the first and most crucial leadership challenge that every leader must face\
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Redefined Leaders\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 are always teaching and learning\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 mold brilliant and eminent men and women\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 persevere\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 energize themselves by the sheer ambition of their heroic goals\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 innovate by approaching their challenges in ways their predecessors never imagined\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 devote themselves to excellence\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 remain open to new ideas, even in old age\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 honor truth above egos\
\ls4\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 influence others by their example, their ideas and their coaching\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 We do not have a defining \'93moment,\'94 rather, a pattern is slowly etched through a lifetime studded with ordinary opportunities to make subtle differences\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 To Order One\'92s Life\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Only those that know their weaknesses can deal with them or even hope to conquer them\
\ls5\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
